**1. `types/api-developer.ts`** -- Type definitions

```typescript
export interface ApiKey {
  id: string;
  key: string; // e.g., "cb_sk_live_..."
  name: string;
  createdAt: string;
  lastUsedAt: string | null;
  status: 'active' | 'revoked';
  permissions: string[];
}

export interface ApiEndpoint {
  method: 'GET' | 'POST' | 'PUT' | 'DELETE';
  path: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  parameters: Array<{
    name: string;
    type: string;
    required: boolean;
    description: string;
    example: string;
  }>;
  responseExample: string; // JSON string
  creditCost: number;
}

export interface WebhookConfig {
  id: string;
  url: string;
  events: string[];
  secret: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  createdAt: string;
  lastDelivery: string | null;
}

export interface ApiUsagePoint {
  date: string;
  requests: number;
  errors: number;
  latencyMs: number;
}

export interface RateLimitInfo {
  plan: 'free' | 'pro' | 'enterprise';
  dailyLimit: number;
  used: number;
  remaining: number;
  resetAt: string;
}
```

**2. `services/api-developer.ts`** -- API developer hub service

Functions:
- `getApiKeys(): ApiKey[]` -- reads from localStorage `citedby_api_keys`
- `generateApiKey(name: string): ApiKey` -- creates a new key with random string (`cb_sk_live_${random}`)
- `revokeApiKey(keyId: string)` -- sets status to 'revoked'
- `regenerateApiKey(keyId: string): ApiKey` -- revokes old, creates new with same name
- `getEndpoints(): ApiEndpoint[]` -- returns the hardcoded endpoint definitions with examples
- `getWebhooks(): WebhookConfig[]` -- reads from localStorage `citedby_webhooks`
- `addWebhook(url: string, events: string[]): WebhookConfig`
- `removeWebhook(id: string)`
- `toggleWebhook(id: string)`
- `getRateLimits(plan: string): RateLimitInfo`
- `getUsageAnalytics(days: number): ApiUsagePoint[]` -- returns deterministic simulated usage data
- `generateCodeExample(endpoint: ApiEndpoint, apiKey: string, language: 'curl' | 'javascript' | 'python'): string` -- generates code snippets

